radiographic_examinations.findings: A tubular structure in the expected region of the appendix measures up to 9 mm in caliber, highly suspicious for appendicitis. Small quantity of fluid in the right paracolic gutter. Prominent lymph nodes in the pericecal region, measuring up to 8 mm, likely reactive. Small-to-moderate quantity of free fluid in the pelvis. No evidence of abscess formation or free intraperitoneal air.
